COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1166, L.D. 1748
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment provides that
55 the Department of Labor is required to partner with state entities, including the Public
66 Utilities Commission, the Governor’s Energy Office and the Office of Policy Innovation
77 and the Future, or successor governmental departments and offices having jurisdiction over
88 energy matters, to develop a fact sheet and technical resource guide that outlines the
99 requirements, opportunities, expectations and responsibilities detailed in state labor laws,
1100 rules and priority selection opportunities for entities developing assisted projects in the
1111 State with a nameplate capacity of one megawatt or more. The responsible entity
1122 developing an assisted project and its prime contracting entity must each separately attest
1133 under penalty of perjury that each entity has reviewed the fact sheet and technical resource
1144 guide and that each entity is aware of resources available to assist in the entity’s
1155 understanding and compliance and that all contractors and subcontractors are aware of the
1166 requirements in the fact sheet and technical resource guide. The amendment also requires
1177 that the department supply an annual report to the joint standing committee of the
1188 Legislature having jurisdiction over labor matters beginning February 15, 2027.
1199 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
